3) Lambda Expressions

⭐11. What is Lambda Expression?
Answer:
Lambda is short form of method(anonymous function).
Lambda is a short way to implement a functional interface without creating a class.
Concise way to implement functional interface.

Example:
Runnable r = () -> System.out.println("Hello");

⭐12. Why lambda was introduced?
Answer:
To reduce boilerplate code and support functional programming in Java.

⭐13. Syntax of lambda?
Answer:
(parameters) -> expression/body
(parameters) -> {statements}

Example:
 	(a, b) -> a + b
 	x -> x*x
 	() -> System.out.println("Hello")

⭐14. Can lambda be used without functional interface?
Answer:
No. Lambda always needs a functional interface type to work.


⭐15. Can lambda access local variables?
Answer:
Yes, but local variables must be effectively final (not modified after initialization).

