9) Collectors (Most Important)

✅ What is Collectors?
It converts stream back into a collection like List/Set/Map
Collectors is used to collect stream output into:
✅ List
✅ Set
✅ Map
and do grouping/counting

✅ Example: collect to List
import java.util.*;
import java.util.stream.*;

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        List<Integer> nums = Arrays.asList(1,2,3,4,5,6);

        List<Integer> evenList = nums.stream()
                .filter(x -> x % 2 == 0)
                .collect(Collectors.toList());

        System.out.println(evenList); // [2, 4, 6]
    }
}

✅ Example: collect to Set (removes duplicates)
import java.util.*;
import java.util.stream.*;

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        List<Integer> nums = Arrays.asList(10,10,20,30,30);

        Set<Integer> unique = nums.stream()
                .collect(Collectors.toSet());

        System.out.println(unique); // [20, 10, 30]
    }
}
